AB  - The article deals with musictherapeutic pain management. It focusses on performative and meaningful aspects that emanate from working with sounds that represent feelings of pain and the imagination of healing or soothing the pain. A case study of an inpatient suffering from chronic somatoform back pain illustrates the specific therapeutic model that is presented here. Epidemiologic facts, outcomes of research and a psychodynamic approach build the framework for some conclusions on processes that are effectively involved in the restitution of the patient's abilities to deal with the pain disorder and the psychosocial issues connected with it. (PsycInfo Database Record (c) 2021 APA, all rights reserved)
